        <abstract> 
<p>Thanks for <hi rend="italic">Begonia</hi> and <hi rend="italic">Oxalis</hi>.</p> 
            <p>Keeps obstinate about crossing and could argue till doomsday, but will not bother JDH.</p> 
<p>Sees that JDH has finished <hi rend="italic">Welwitschia</hi>.</p> 
            <p>Thinks Huxley’s Working Men’s Lectures excellent.</p> 
<p>Has finished <hi rend="italic">Linum</hi> paper [<hi rend="italic">Collected papers</hi> 2: 93–105],</p>  
<p>and abstract of Bates’s paper for <hi rend="italic">Natural History Review</hi>,</p>  
<p>and has begun to arrange concluding chapters [for <hi rend="italic">Variation</hi>]. Is paralysed on how to begin.</p> 
        </abstract>
